task.summary: Change CreateSite back to single children for each link. Change ReadSiteRevsFile to read this layout.

Create EditOrDeleteSite and DeleteFileOrFolder classes to handle modifying or deleting a site.
Change CreateSite class so that it can be used for either creating a site or modifying a site. Add indents to xml file creation.
Add and implement a delete button to the edit site tab with a YES/NO dialog for confirmation.
Adding ability to rename a site

Checking for the existence of a site in the create site action listener instead of in the CreateSite class.
This keeps a 'site already exists' error message from occurring when renaming a site.

Changing nameOfEditSite to only display the site name instead of the full path
This also required changing the save changes and delete site action listeners to build the path instead of just reading this field.

Create SiteManipulator class to handle creating and deleting site entities
This class takes the place of the CreateSite, DeleteFileOrFolder, and EditOrDeleteSite classes. Still need to create the calling swing worker class.
Create RestoreSite.java and modify ReadSiteRevsFile.java to work with both reading in fields and restoring a site. Add calls from MainUI to restore a site.

Adding WindowsShortcut.java from StackOverflow to parse the actual file out of the link used in gcc versions switcher.
Implementing changes in RestoreSite.java to utilize WindowsShortcut.
Changing button label under the Directories tab from Change Site Directory to Change Files Directory.
